                  </hi>. I am a policeman. On Friday, the 27th of October, at ten minutes before six o'clock, I saw the prisoner in Museum-street, with the blanket under his arm—I took him into custody,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183711270067"></xptr>
               <p>I then made inquiry, and found it had been taken from Elliott's—he said a boy gave it him.</p>
               <p>
